==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Spinny
<hw>Spin"ny</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Spinnies</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[OF.
<ets>espinaye</ets>,<ets>espinoye</ets>, <ets>espinei</ets>,
<ets>espanoi</ets>, F. <ets>⟦eacute⟧pinaie</ets>, from L.
<ets>spinetum</ets> a thicket of thorns, fr. <ets>spina</ets> a thorn.
See <er>Spine</er>.]</ety> <def>A small thicket or grove with
undergrowth; a clump of trees.</def> <altsp>[Written also
<asp>spinney</asp>, and <asp>spinny</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The downs rise steep, crowned with black fir
<qex>spinnies</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>C. Kingsley.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Spinny</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Spinny
<hw>Spin"ny</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Cf. <er>Spiny</er>,
<pos>a.</pos>]</ety> <def>Thin and long; slim; slender.</def>
<mark>[Obs. or Prov. Eng.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Spinose</ent>⟦br⟧
